Why move from a JSON file to a database?
Using a JSON file is cool for small apps or testing, but it gets messy fast. It’s not great when multiple users are working with the data, or when the app grows. A database is faster, more reliable, and easier to manage at scale.

Choose your database
pick a database to use PostgreSQL, MySQL, or MongoDB.

Set up the database
 install the database and create a place (called a “table” or “collection”) that matches the kind of data you were storing in the JSON file. For example, if the JSON had tasks with a title and a status (done or not), i will make a database table with those same fields.

Right now, my app  reads the JSON file and updates it directly. i can change that part so it talks to the database instead — asking for data, saving new items, updating stuff, etc. i will basically replacing file reading/writing with database queries.

Once my app is fully using the database and everything works, i don’t need the JSON file anymore. i can delete it and rely fully on the database.





